## TransformNode.getType() method

Gets the output type based on input types

**Signature:**

```typescript
protected getType(): "" | "vec2" | "vec3" | "vec4" | "mat2" | "mat3" | "mat4";
```
**Returns:**

"" \| "vec2" \| "vec3" \| "vec4" \| "mat2" \| "mat3" \| "mat4"

The result type of the transformation, or empty string if invalid

## Remarks

Result type rules: - vec \* mat = vec (same dimension) - mat \* vec = vec (same dimension) - mat \* mat = mat (same dimension)
